# Example cluster list file
# One cluster ID per line (no comments or blank lines in actual file)
#
# To use this file:
#   1. Copy to clusters.list: cp examples/clusters.list.example clusters.list
#   2. Replace with your actual cluster IDs
#   3. Run: ./collect_from_multiple_clusters.sh --cluster-list clusters.list -r "TICKET-123"
#
# Example cluster IDs (replace with real ones):
# abc123def456ghi789
# xyz789uvw456rst123
# pqr456mno789jkl012
